comment: Drummond (DET) makes body to body contact with Whiteside (MIA) that affects his SQBR.
Drummond (DET) and Johnson (MIA) briefly engage and separate off ball.
Drummond (DET) never fully clears the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
McGruder (MIA) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Harris (DET) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
[Detectable with stop watch] Whiteside (MIA) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Drummond (DET) makes marginal contact with Dragic (MIA) prior to the pass.
Dragic (MIA) makes incidental contact with Caldwell-Pope (DET) during rebounding.
Drummond (DET) sets the screen on Johnson (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Baynes (DET) sets the screen on Johnson (MIA) and continues moving into him, affecting his ability to defend the play.
Johnson (DET) steps over the sideline and makes contact with the inbound passer.
Whiteside (MIA) sets the screen on Smith (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Johnson (MIA) makes marginal contact with Caldwell-Pope (DET) that does not affect his SQBR.
McGruder (MIA) intentionally kicks the ball on the play.
Dragic (MIA) makes incidental contact with Johnson (DET) prior to the held ball that does not affect his SQBR.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) cleanly steals the ball from Dragic (MIA).
Dragic (MIA) makes marginal contact with Caldwell-Pope (DET) during the loose ball.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) steps out of bounds while in possession of the ball.
Whiteside (MIA) sets the screen on Harris (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
McGruder (MIA) dislodges Smith (DET) during rebounding.
Whiteside (MIA) grabs and pulls Drummond's (DET) jersey, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Harris (DET) makes incidental contact with Dragic (MIA) that does not affect his shot attempt or ability to control the ball.
Whiteside (MIA) makes incidental contact with Drummond (DET) during rebounding.
Drummond (DET) makes contact with the rim, but does not cause the ball to make an unnatural bounce.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Whiteside (MIA) released his field goal attempt prior to the game clock expiring is confirmed.
